SUMMARY:Maker Mini: Designing Projects to Account for Wood Movement
DESCRIPTION:MAKE Roanoke\nJoin us at MAKE Roanoke for another FREE Maker M
 ini!\n\nThis lecture will focus on how wood naturally moves and how to acc
 ount for this movement when designing wooden projects. We'll focus on mate
 rial choice\, glueing methods\, and different ways of attaching tabletops.
 \n\nThis Maker Mini is recommended for those age 12 and up\, and it is sui
 table for beginner to intermediate woodworkers.\n\n**Please note that MAKE
  Roanoke is an active workshop:**\n\n* All participants must have a signed
  waiver on file. If the participant is a minor\, the waiver must be signed
  by a parent or court-appointed legal guardian. Waivers can be filled out 
 ahead of time at [https://mkroa.org/waiver](https://mkroa.org/waiver "http
 s://mkroa.org/waiver")\n* Children who are not participating in the event 
 are not permitted in the space.\n* Closed toed shoes are required in the s
 pace at all times by everyone\, regardless of age or participation in an e
 vent. No sandals\, crocs\, or bare feet.\n* You may be asked to remove or 
 tuck in dangling jewelry\, lanyards\, etc for safety.\n* Depending on the 
 activity\, other dress code rules may apply.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/make-roanoke/events/313315057/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260211T205636Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260211T205636Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
