SUMMARY:MEMBERS (& Guests) ONLY: Community Craft Day
DESCRIPTION:MAKE Roanoke\nCome work on whatever project you want and enjoy
  the company of fellow MAKE Roanoke Members! Carve out some time to create
  for the sake of creating! From coloring to making hats to restoring machi
 nery\, this is a social night of crafting of all kinds for makers of all k
 inds!\n\nBring some dough to chip in for dinner if you want some!\n\nThis 
 event runs from 4-8pm and is for MAKE Roanoke members and guests.\n\n**Ple
 ase note that MAKE Roanoke is an active workshop:**\n\n* All participants 
 must have a signed waiver on file. If the participant is a minor\, the wai
 ver must be signed by a parent or court-appointed legal guardian. Waivers 
 can be filled out ahead of time at https://mkroa.org/waiver\n* Children wh
 o are not participating in the event are not permitted in the space.\n* **
 Closed toed shoes are required** in the space at all times by everyone\, r
 egardless of age or participation in an event. No sandals\, crocs\, or bar
 e feet.\n* You may be asked to remove or tuck in dangling jewelry\, lanyar
 ds\, etc. for safety.\n* Guests\, and members not signed off on yellow/red
  tools\, are only permitted to use green level tools\, but feel free to br
 ing your own tools to create something fun!
