SUMMARY:Maker Mini: Multi-Material 3D Printing with Orcaslicer
DESCRIPTION:MAKE Roanoke\nJoin us at MAKE Roanoke with another FREE Maker 
 Mini as we show you techniques to achieve a multi-material or multi-color 
 3D Print!\n\nThis Maker Mini introduces the fundamentals of using OrcaSlic
 er for multi-material and multicolor 3D printing. Students will learn how 
 to assign different materials or colors to specific parts of a model\, opt
 imize print time\, and set up dissimilar material supports for clean overh
 angs. We’ll cover preparing multi-body models\, using painting tools\, a
 nd managing filament changes.\n\n**Students are encouraged to bring a lapt
 op with Orcaslicer to follow along if desired.**\n\nThis Maker Mini is FRE
 E and open to the public\, you do NOT need to be a MAKE Roanoke member to 
 attend. It is recommended for ages 14 and up.\n\n**Please note that MAKE R
 oanoke is an active workshop:**\n\n* All participants must have a signed w
 aiver on file. If the participant is a minor\, the waiver must be signed b
 y a parent or court-appointed legal guardian. Waivers can be filled out ah
 ead of time at https://mkroa.org/waiver\n* Children who are not participat
 ing in the event are not permitted in the space.\n* Closed toed shoes are 
 required in the space at all times by everyone\, regardless of age or part
 icipation in an event. No sandals\, crocs\, or bare feet.\n* You may be as
 ked to remove or tuck in dangling jewelry\, lanyards\, etc for safety.\n* 
 Depending on the activity\, other dress code rules may apply.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/make-roanoke/events/313432308/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260219T173818Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260219T173818Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
